						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the south verandah of south <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> inside the old <hi rend="italic">vāhanamaṇḍapa,</hi> Tiruvīraṭṭānēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 14: 985 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that an individual, Pūṅgunṟam-uḍaiyāṉ Asadāmaṉ Ayyāṟan <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Kaṇḍatōḷkaṇḍappaiyan of Kīḻāṉmūr-nāḍu had caused a <hi rend="italic">nāṭakaśālai</hi> constructed for Tiruvīraṭṭānam-uḍaiyār at Tiruvadigai and made a gift of ninety-six sheep for burning a perpetual lamp probably in the auditorium.</p>						

						</summary>
